Description: User-space Linux driver for the HP Internet Handset (G9)
 Driver and daemon for the Hewlett-Packard Internet Handset (USB
 03f0:1c07, firmware G9 v1.0.0.0). Provides:
 .
   * A `handset` command for controlling the device (ring, speakerphone
     mode, state inspection, reset).
   * A systemd user service that rings the base speaker on incoming
     Rambox calls (WhatsApp and Messenger).
   * A PipeWire virtual sink "HP Handset (Speakerphone)" that makes the
     base speaker available as a regular system audio output.
   * A call-state machine that mimics a real phone:
       - lift handset      -> answer / earpiece
       - cradle (no hold)  -> hang up
       - hold then cradle  -> hands-free via base speaker
       - big-N off cradle  -> end hands-free call
 .
 The device works as a class-compliant USB Audio + HID device; this
 package only adds the routing logic and user-facing controls.
